Note:
BACK_PRESSURE - Reactive Streams 1.0 compatible back-pressure
primitives.

Three core types:
  BoundedBuffer  - mutex+condvar protected ring buffer optimised for
                   streaming (producer blocks when full, consumer blocks
                   when empty).
  Publisher      - exposes a subscribe(subscriber) operation; tracks all
                   active subscriptions.
  Subscriber     - receives onNext/onComplete/onError callbacks driven
                   by demand expressed via Subscription.request(n).
  Subscription   - per-(publisher, subscriber) demand counter; cancel
                   marks the subscription stopped.

BoundedBuffer layout (72 bytes):
  offset 0:  mutex_ptr        (8 bytes)
  offset 8:  not_full_cv      (8 bytes)
  offset 16: not_empty_cv     (8 bytes)
  offset 24: buffer_ptr       (8 bytes) - ring of 8-byte slots
  offset 32: capacity         (8 bytes)
  offset 40: head             (8 bytes) - next read index
  offset 48: tail             (8 bytes) - next write index
  offset 56: count            (8 bytes) - number of buffered elements
  offset 64: closed_flag      (8 bytes) - 1 once buffer is closed

Publisher layout (40 bytes):
  offset 0:  mutex_ptr        (8 bytes)
  offset 8:  subscriptions    (8 bytes) - linked list head
  offset 16: source_fn        (8 bytes) - Process pointer; pull-mode source
  offset 24: source_state     (8 bytes) - opaque user state
  offset 32: subscription_count (8 bytes)

Subscriber layout (32 bytes):
  offset 0:  on_next_fn       (8 bytes) - (subscriber_state, value) -> Integer
  offset 8:  on_complete_fn   (8 bytes) - (subscriber_state) -> Integer
  offset 16: on_error_fn      (8 bytes) - (subscriber_state, error) -> Integer
  offset 24: state_ptr        (8 bytes)

Subscription layout (48 bytes):
  offset 0:  publisher        (8 bytes)
  offset 8:  subscriber       (8 bytes)
  offset 16: pending_demand   (8 bytes)
  offset 24: cancelled_flag   (8 bytes)
  offset 32: mutex_ptr        (8 bytes)
  offset 40: next             (8 bytes) - publisher's linked-list pointer

Dependencies:
- threading/sync_core.runa
- memory/layout.runa
- core/memory_core.runa
- streams/stream.runa (for adapter into pull stream)
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/threading/sync_core.runa" as Sync
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Mem
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/streams/stream.runa" as Stream

Note: BoundedBuffer constants
Constant BB_OFF_MUTEX as Integer is 0
Constant BB_OFF_NOT_FULL as Integer is 8
Constant BB_OFF_NOT_EMPTY as Integer is 16
Constant BB_OFF_BUFFER as Integer is 24
Constant BB_OFF_CAPACITY as Integer is 32
Constant BB_OFF_HEAD as Integer is 40
Constant BB_OFF_TAIL as Integer is 48
Constant BB_OFF_COUNT as Integer is 56
Constant BB_OFF_CLOSED as Integer is 64
Constant BB_STRUCT_SIZE as Integer is 72

Constant BB_OK as Integer is 1
Constant BB_ERR_INVALID as Integer is 0
Constant BB_ERR_CLOSED as Integer is -1
Constant BB_ERR_FULL as Integer is -2
Constant BB_ERR_EMPTY as Integer is -3

Note: Publisher / Subscriber / Subscription constants
Constant PUB_OFF_MUTEX as Integer is 0
Constant PUB_OFF_SUBS as Integer is 8
Constant PUB_OFF_SOURCE_FN as Integer is 16
Constant PUB_OFF_SOURCE_STATE as Integer is 24
Constant PUB_OFF_COUNT as Integer is 32
Constant PUB_STRUCT_SIZE as Integer is 40

Constant SUB_OFF_ON_NEXT as Integer is 0
Constant SUB_OFF_ON_COMPLETE as Integer is 8
Constant SUB_OFF_ON_ERROR as Integer is 16
Constant SUB_OFF_STATE as Integer is 24
Constant SUB_STRUCT_SIZE as Integer is 32

Constant SUBN_OFF_PUB as Integer is 0
Constant SUBN_OFF_SUBR as Integer is 8
Constant SUBN_OFF_DEMAND as Integer is 16
Constant SUBN_OFF_CANCELLED as Integer is 24
Constant SUBN_OFF_MUTEX as Integer is 32
Constant SUBN_OFF_NEXT as Integer is 40
Constant SUBN_STRUCT_SIZE as Integer is 48

Constant SUBN_OK as Integer is 1
Constant SUBN_ERR_INVALID as Integer is 0
Constant SUBN_ERR_CANCELLED as Integer is -1
Constant SUBN_ERR_NO_DEMAND as Integer is -2

Constant SOURCE_OK as Integer is 1
Constant SOURCE_COMPLETE as Integer is 0
Constant SOURCE_ERROR as Integer is -1

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Indirect-call shims — real x86_64 indirect dispatch via inline assembly.
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "bp_runtime_call_indirect_2" takes fn as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: fn at [rbp-8], a at [rbp-16], b at [rbp-24], result at [rbp-32].
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        mov rax, qword ptr [rbp-8]
        mov rdi, qword ptr [rbp-16]
        mov rsi, qword ptr [rbp-24]
        call rax
        mov qword ptr [rbp-32], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bp_runtime_call_indirect_1" takes fn as Integer, a as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: fn at [rbp-8], a at [rbp-16], result at [rbp-24].
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        mov rax, qword ptr [rbp-8]
        mov rdi, qword ptr [rbp-16]
        call rax
        mov qword ptr [rbp-24], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: BoundedBuffer
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
A BoundedBuffer is a ring buffer optimised for streaming: producers
block on not_full while the buffer is at capacity, consumers block on
not_empty while it is empty. It is similar to channel.runa but holds a
contiguous buffer rather than a linked list, which keeps cache locality
high in steady state.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate the 72-byte record, allocate the ring (capacity * 8 bytes),
create one mutex and two condvars. Initialise indices to zero.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Each enqueue/dequeue pays one mutex acquire. condvar signalling is
issued only when transitioning across the empty/full boundaries.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Heap-owned; close() prevents further writes but allows the consumer to
drain remaining items.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "bounded_buffer_create" takes capacity as Integer returns Integer:
    If capacity is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let b be proc allocate from Memory with BB_STRUCT_SIZE
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mtx be proc mutex_create from Sync
    If mtx is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Memory with b
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cv_full be proc condvar_create from Sync
    If cv_full is equal to 0:
        proc mutex_destroy from Sync with mtx
        proc deallocate from Memory with b
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cv_empty be proc condvar_create from Sync
    If cv_empty is equal to 0:
        proc condvar_destroy from Sync with cv_full
        proc mutex_destroy from Sync with mtx
        proc deallocate from Memory with b
        Return 0
    End If
    Let buf_bytes be capacity multiplied by 8
    Let buf be proc allocate from Memory with buf_bytes
    If buf is equal to 0:
        proc condvar_destroy from Sync with cv_empty
        proc condvar_destroy from Sync with cv_full
        proc mutex_destroy from Sync with mtx
        proc deallocate from Memory with b
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_MUTEX, mtx
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_NOT_FULL, cv_full
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_NOT_EMPTY, cv_empty
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_BUFFER, buf
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_CAPACITY, capacity
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_HEAD, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_TAIL, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_COUNT, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_CLOSED, 0
    Return b
End Process

Process called "bounded_buffer_destroy" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return BB_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    Let mtx be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_MUTEX
    Let cv_full be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_NOT_FULL
    Let cv_empty be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_NOT_EMPTY
    Let buf be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_BUFFER
    If buf is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Memory with buf
    End If
    If cv_full is not equal to 0:
        proc condvar_destroy from Sync with cv_full
    End If
    If cv_empty is not equal to 0:
        proc condvar_destroy from Sync with cv_empty
    End If
    If mtx is not equal to 0:
        proc mutex_destroy from Sync with mtx
    End If
    proc deallocate from Memory with b
    Return BB_OK
End Process

Process called "bounded_buffer_capacity" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_CAPACITY
End Process

Process called "bounded_buffer_count" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mtx be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_MUTEX
    proc mutex_lock from Sync with mtx
    Let c be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_COUNT
    proc mutex_unlock from Sync with mtx
    Return c
End Process

Process called "bounded_buffer_is_closed" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_CLOSED
End Process

@Reasoning
push blocks the calling thread until there is room in the buffer or it
has been closed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Acquire mutex; while count == capacity and not closed, wait on
not_full. On closure return BB_ERR_CLOSED. Otherwise store the value
at tail, advance tail mod capacity, increment count, signal not_empty
and release.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
One mutex acquire; at most one condvar signal per push.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Concurrent push from multiple producers is safe (they serialise on the
mutex).
@End Security_Scope

Process called "bounded_buffer_push" takes b as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return BB_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    Let mtx be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_MUTEX
    Let cv_full be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_NOT_FULL
    Let cv_empty be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_NOT_EMPTY
    proc mutex_lock from Sync with mtx
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let closed be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_CLOSED
        If closed is equal to 1:
            proc mutex_unlock from Sync with mtx
            Return BB_ERR_CLOSED
        End If
        Let count be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_COUNT
        Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_CAPACITY
        If count is less than capacity:
            Let tail be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_TAIL
            Let buf be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_BUFFER
            Let off be tail multiplied by 8
            proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with buf, off, value
            Let new_tail be tail plus 1
            If new_tail is greater than or equal to capacity:
                Set new_tail to 0
            End If
            proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_TAIL, new_tail
            proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_COUNT, (count plus 1)
            proc condvar_signal from Sync with cv_empty
            proc mutex_unlock from Sync with mtx
            Return BB_OK
        End If
        proc condvar_wait from Sync with cv_full, mtx
    End While
    proc mutex_unlock from Sync with mtx
    Return BB_ERR_INVALID
End Process

Process called "bounded_buffer_try_push" takes b as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return BB_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    Let mtx be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_MUTEX
    Let cv_empty be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_NOT_EMPTY
    proc mutex_lock from Sync with mtx
    Let closed be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_CLOSED
    If closed is equal to 1:
        proc mutex_unlock from Sync with mtx
        Return BB_ERR_CLOSED
    End If
    Let count be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_COUNT
    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_CAPACITY
    If count is greater than or equal to capacity:
        proc mutex_unlock from Sync with mtx
        Return BB_ERR_FULL
    End If
    Let tail be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_TAIL
    Let buf be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_BUFFER
    Let off be tail multiplied by 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with buf, off, value
    Let new_tail be tail plus 1
    If new_tail is greater than or equal to capacity:
        Set new_tail to 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_TAIL, new_tail
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_COUNT, (count plus 1)
    proc condvar_signal from Sync with cv_empty
    proc mutex_unlock from Sync with mtx
    Return BB_OK
End Process

@Reasoning
pop blocks until at least one element is available or the buffer is
closed AND empty.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Acquire mutex; while count == 0 and not closed, wait on not_empty.
When closed and empty, return BB_ERR_CLOSED. Otherwise read at head,
advance head mod capacity, decrement count, signal not_full and release.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
One mutex acquire; at most one condvar signal per pop.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Concurrent pops are safe.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "bounded_buffer_pop" takes b as Integer, out_holder as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return BB_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    If out_holder is equal to 0:
        Return BB_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    Let mtx be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_MUTEX
    Let cv_full be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_NOT_FULL
    Let cv_empty be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_NOT_EMPTY
    proc mutex_lock from Sync with mtx
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let count be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_COUNT
        If count is greater than 0:
            Let head be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_HEAD
            Let buf be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_BUFFER
            Let off be head multiplied by 8
            Let value be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with buf, off
            Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_CAPACITY
            Let new_head be head plus 1
            If new_head is greater than or equal to capacity:
                Set new_head to 0
            End If
            proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_HEAD, new_head
            proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_COUNT, (count minus 1)
            proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with out_holder, 0, value
            proc condvar_signal from Sync with cv_full
            proc mutex_unlock from Sync with mtx
            Return BB_OK
        End If
        Let closed be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_CLOSED
        If closed is equal to 1:
            proc mutex_unlock from Sync with mtx
            Return BB_ERR_CLOSED
        End If
        proc condvar_wait from Sync with cv_empty, mtx
    End While
    proc mutex_unlock from Sync with mtx
    Return BB_ERR_INVALID
End Process

Process called "bounded_buffer_try_pop" takes b as Integer, out_holder as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return BB_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    If out_holder is equal to 0:
        Return BB_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    Let mtx be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_MUTEX
    Let cv_full be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_NOT_FULL
    proc mutex_lock from Sync with mtx
    Let count be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_COUNT
    If count is equal to 0:
        Let closed be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_CLOSED
        proc mutex_unlock from Sync with mtx
        If closed is equal to 1:
            Return BB_ERR_CLOSED
        End If
        Return BB_ERR_EMPTY
    End If
    Let head be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_HEAD
    Let buf be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_BUFFER
    Let off be head multiplied by 8
    Let value be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with buf, off
    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_CAPACITY
    Let new_head be head plus 1
    If new_head is greater than or equal to capacity:
        Set new_head to 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_HEAD, new_head
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_COUNT, (count minus 1)
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with out_holder, 0, value
    proc condvar_signal from Sync with cv_full
    proc mutex_unlock from Sync with mtx
    Return BB_OK
End Process

Process called "bounded_buffer_close" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return BB_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    Let mtx be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_MUTEX
    Let cv_full be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_NOT_FULL
    Let cv_empty be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_NOT_EMPTY
    proc mutex_lock from Sync with mtx
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with b, BB_OFF_CLOSED, 1
    proc condvar_broadcast from Sync with cv_full
    proc condvar_broadcast from Sync with cv_empty
    proc mutex_unlock from Sync with mtx
    Return BB_OK
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Publisher / Subscriber / Subscription
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Publisher is the source side of a Reactive Streams pipeline. It holds a
pull-mode source function (state, out_holder) -> Integer; this matches
the stream.runa next-fn protocol. The publisher maintains a linked
list of Subscriptions to broadcast onNext/onComplete/onError.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 40 bytes, create a mutex protecting the subscription list,
zero the head pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
One allocation + one mutex_create per publisher.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller owns the source function and state. The publisher does not free
state when destroyed; callers should release it explicitly.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "publisher_create" takes source_fn as Integer, source_state as Integer returns Integer:
    Let p be proc allocate from Memory with PUB_STRUCT_SIZE
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mtx be proc mutex_create from Sync
    If mtx is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Memory with p
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with p, PUB_OFF_MUTEX, mtx
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with p, PUB_OFF_SUBS, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with p, PUB_OFF_SOURCE_FN, source_fn
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with p, PUB_OFF_SOURCE_STATE, source_state
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with p, PUB_OFF_COUNT, 0
    Return p
End Process

Process called "publisher_destroy" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return SUBN_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    Let mtx be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with p, PUB_OFF_MUTEX
    proc mutex_lock from Sync with mtx
    Let head be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with p, PUB_OFF_SUBS
    While head is not equal to 0:
        Let next_n be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with head, SUBN_OFF_NEXT
        Let sub_mtx be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with head, SUBN_OFF_MUTEX
        If sub_mtx is not equal to 0:
            proc mutex_destroy from Sync with sub_mtx
        End If
        proc deallocate from Memory with head
        Set head to next_n
    End While
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with p, PUB_OFF_SUBS, 0
    proc mutex_unlock from Sync with mtx
    proc mutex_destroy from Sync with mtx
    proc deallocate from Memory with p
    Return SUBN_OK
End Process

Process called "publisher_subscription_count" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mtx be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with p, PUB_OFF_MUTEX
    proc mutex_lock from Sync with mtx
    Let n be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with p, PUB_OFF_COUNT
    proc mutex_unlock from Sync with mtx
    Return n
End Process

Process called "subscriber_create" takes on_next_fn as Integer, on_complete_fn as Integer, on_error_fn as Integer, state_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    Let s be proc allocate from Memory with SUB_STRUCT_SIZE
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with s, SUB_OFF_ON_NEXT, on_next_fn
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with s, SUB_OFF_ON_COMPLETE, on_complete_fn
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with s, SUB_OFF_ON_ERROR, on_error_fn
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with s, SUB_OFF_STATE, state_ptr
    Return s
End Process

Process called "subscriber_destroy" takes s as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return SUBN_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    proc deallocate from Memory with s
    Return SUBN_OK
End Process

@Reasoning
subscribe links a subscriber to a publisher and returns a Subscription
the consumer uses to express demand. The publisher pushes the new node
to the head of its subscription list.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate a Subscription record with its own mutex, store publisher and
subscriber pointers, initialise demand to zero, splice into the
publisher's list.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
One allocation + one mutex_create per subscribe call.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The returned subscription is owned by the publisher's destroy; do not
free it manually.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "publisher_subscribe" takes publisher as Integer, subscriber as Integer returns Integer:
    If publisher is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If subscriber is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let subn be proc allocate from Memory with SUBN_STRUCT_SIZE
    If subn is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mtx be proc mutex_create from Sync
    If mtx is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Memory with subn
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_PUB, publisher
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_SUBR, subscriber
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_DEMAND, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_CANCELLED, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_MUTEX, mtx
    Let pmtx be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with publisher, PUB_OFF_MUTEX
    proc mutex_lock from Sync with pmtx
    Let head be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with publisher, PUB_OFF_SUBS
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_NEXT, head
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with publisher, PUB_OFF_SUBS, subn
    Let cnt be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with publisher, PUB_OFF_COUNT
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with publisher, PUB_OFF_COUNT, (cnt plus 1)
    proc mutex_unlock from Sync with pmtx
    Return subn
End Process

Process called "subscription_pending_demand" takes subn as Integer returns Integer:
    If subn is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mtx be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_MUTEX
    proc mutex_lock from Sync with mtx
    Let d be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_DEMAND
    proc mutex_unlock from Sync with mtx
    Return d
End Process

Process called "subscription_is_cancelled" takes subn as Integer returns Integer:
    If subn is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let mtx be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_MUTEX
    proc mutex_lock from Sync with mtx
    Let c be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_CANCELLED
    proc mutex_unlock from Sync with mtx
    Return c
End Process

Process called "subscription_cancel" takes subn as Integer returns Integer:
    If subn is equal to 0:
        Return SUBN_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    Let mtx be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_MUTEX
    proc mutex_lock from Sync with mtx
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_CANCELLED, 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_DEMAND, 0
    proc mutex_unlock from Sync with mtx
    Return SUBN_OK
End Process

@Reasoning
subscription_request expresses demand: the consumer is ready to receive
up to n additional onNext callbacks. The publisher fulfils outstanding
demand by pulling from its source until either demand or source is
exhausted.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Add n to pending_demand under the subscription mutex. Then attempt to
drain demand: while demand > 0 and source has data, pull a value via
the indirect shim, dispatch on_next to the subscriber, decrement demand.
On source completion deliver on_complete and cancel the subscription.
On source error deliver on_error and cancel.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Demand drain is single-threaded per subscription, so the inner loop is
lock-free past the initial demand update.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The source function must be safe to call from the requesting thread.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "subscription_request" takes subn as Integer, n as Integer returns Integer:
    If subn is equal to 0:
        Return SUBN_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    If n is less than or equal to 0:
        Return SUBN_OK
    End If
    Let sub_mtx be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_MUTEX
    proc mutex_lock from Sync with sub_mtx
    Let cancelled be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_CANCELLED
    If cancelled is equal to 1:
        proc mutex_unlock from Sync with sub_mtx
        Return SUBN_ERR_CANCELLED
    End If
    Let prior_demand be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_DEMAND
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_DEMAND, (prior_demand plus n)
    proc mutex_unlock from Sync with sub_mtx

    Let publisher be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_PUB
    Let subscriber be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_SUBR
    Let source_fn be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with publisher, PUB_OFF_SOURCE_FN
    Let source_state be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with publisher, PUB_OFF_SOURCE_STATE
    Let on_next be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with subscriber, SUB_OFF_ON_NEXT
    Let on_complete be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with subscriber, SUB_OFF_ON_COMPLETE
    Let on_error be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with subscriber, SUB_OFF_ON_ERROR
    Let subscriber_state be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with subscriber, SUB_OFF_STATE

    Let scratch be proc allocate from Memory with 8
    If scratch is equal to 0:
        Return SUBN_ERR_INVALID
    End If

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        proc mutex_lock from Sync with sub_mtx
        Let demand be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_DEMAND
        Let cancel_check be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_CANCELLED
        If demand is less than or equal to 0:
            proc mutex_unlock from Sync with sub_mtx
            proc deallocate from Memory with scratch
            Return SUBN_OK
        End If
        If cancel_check is equal to 1:
            proc mutex_unlock from Sync with sub_mtx
            proc deallocate from Memory with scratch
            Return SUBN_ERR_CANCELLED
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with subn, SUBN_OFF_DEMAND, (demand minus 1)
        proc mutex_unlock from Sync with sub_mtx

        Let rc be proc bp_runtime_call_indirect_2 with source_fn, source_state, scratch
        If rc is equal to SOURCE_OK:
            Let v be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with scratch, 0
            If on_next is not equal to 0:
                proc bp_runtime_call_indirect_2 with on_next, subscriber_state, v
            End If
        End If
        If rc is equal to SOURCE_COMPLETE:
            If on_complete is not equal to 0:
                proc bp_runtime_call_indirect_1 with on_complete, subscriber_state
            End If
            proc subscription_cancel with subn
            proc deallocate from Memory with scratch
            Return SUBN_OK
        End If
        If rc is equal to SOURCE_ERROR:
            If on_error is not equal to 0:
                proc bp_runtime_call_indirect_2 with on_error, subscriber_state, rc
            End If
            proc subscription_cancel with subn
            proc deallocate from Memory with scratch
            Return SUBN_ERR_CANCELLED
        End If
    End While
    proc deallocate from Memory with scratch
    Return SUBN_OK
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: BoundedBuffer-as-Stream adapter
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Expose a BoundedBuffer as a pull Stream so existing stream transformers
can drain it without reimplementing back-pressure logic.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
The next-fn calls bounded_buffer_pop which blocks until data is
available or the buffer is closed.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
One mutex round-trip per pulled value.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The buffer must outlive the stream.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "bp_buffer_next" takes state as Integer, out_holder as Integer returns Integer:
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rc be proc bounded_buffer_pop with state, out_holder
    If rc is equal to BB_OK:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "proc_address_bp_buffer_next" returns Integer:
    Note: Take the address of bp_buffer_next so the stream layer can store it
    Note: as an Integer-valued function pointer. RIP-relative LEA is position-
    Note: independent and resolves at link time. Result local lives at [rbp-8]
    Note: because this Process has no parameters.
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        lea rax, qword ptr [rip + bp_buffer_next]
        mov qword ptr [rbp-8], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bounded_buffer_to_stream" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc stream_create from Stream with proc_address_bp_buffer_next(), b, 0
End Process
